 Omolabake Fasogbon Organisers of popular television series branded ‘Sokoyokoto’ has announced a re-launch of the show, promising a better and rewarding experience for viewers. The organisers also revealed that cooking show being powered by Flour Mills Nigeria Plc, FMN and Seven up Bottling Company will be featuring two segments. Speaking on the re-launch, Executive Producer of the show, Eduwa Ogungbe explained that the programme was rested two years ago but now re-launching with new exciting features. She said, “For two years now, we have been working assiduously behind the scene to return with more thrilling, stimulating and exhilarating show that would bring the programme back to a foremost position and we have really done that. “The programme will include a unique two segment split- the cooking segment   sponsored by Flour Mills Nigeria and featuring products like Golden Penny Prime Flour, Semovita, pasta, macaroni, Noodles and Aunty B Semolina.” The second part is the main party sponsored by Seven up bottling company plc., bottlers of Pepsi, Aquafina water, Mirinda, Lipton iced tea amongst others. Ogungbe explained further that  top rated artistes  as well as players from different sectors of the economy have been lined up to grace the show who will also  display culinary skills and  party swag before a live audience of over hundred guests. In addition to the cooking contest, she informed that the programme will also have a segment for games, dance and talent contest where winners will get a prize of N20, 000 each. The programme will air on Saturdays and Sundays on designated station.